{
  "texts": [
    "We were concerned about this in answering our second research question, because we had to include cases which were filed before our model's training period, due to a lack of cases filed only afterwards which met our selection criteria.",
    "However, consistently with Blair-Stanek et al.'s (2023) results, there was no indication (in our qualitative analysis of the complaints drafted) that made us suspicious that this was the case in our context (i.e., the ChatGPT-drafted complaint did not generally include facts which were not part of the article in the prompt).",
    "Hallucinations only occurred in three, minor instances.",
    "In two complaints (Hong, et al. v. Block.One, et al., Klingberg v. MGT Capital Investments Inc., et al.), this took the form of ChatGPT inaccurately adding \"John Doe\" defendants, rather than devising specific, fictitious facts.",
    "In the third case (Audet, et al. v. Garza, et al.), the location of a company involved was inconsistent across different sections of the complaint ChatGPT generated."
  ]
}